<TEXT>
<P>
	OMAHA, Neb. (AP) -- A 5-year-old boy died during his youth-league  
baseball game Saturday, collapsing after he was struck in the chest 
by a thrown ball, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	Andrew Cook was standing next to an adult pitcher about 4 p.m.  
when he was hit by a baseball that had been thrown back to the 
pitcher's mound by an adult catcher. 
</P>
<P>
	The boy staggered and fell, took a few breaths and then stopped  
breathing. 
</P>
<P>
	Officer Don Savage said a doctor came out of the stands to join  
others who unsuccessfully tried to revive the child. 
  	   	
