<HEADLINE> Australians Dominate Triathlon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WAIKOLOA, Hawaii (AP) -- Greg Welch fended off fellow Australian  
Chris Hill on Saturday to win the men's division of the Big Island 
Triathlon World Cup. 
</P>
<P>
	Michellie Jones of Australia beat Barbara Lindquist of the  
United States by six seconds to claim the women's title in the 
qualifying race for the 2000 Sydney Olympics. 
</P>
<P>
	Welch completed the 1.5-kilometer ocean swim, 40-kilometer  
bicycle ride and 10-kilometer run in 2 hours, 3 minutes, 15 
seconds, besting Hill by 23 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
	Philippe Fattori of France placed third among the men at  
2:04:19. 
</P>
