<HEADLINE> Dreams Gallore Wins at Belmont </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Dreams Gallore, the prohibitive favorite ridden  
by Robby Albarado, came from off the pace for a decisive 7 1/2-length 
victory in the 43rd running of the $250,000 Mother Goose Stakes for 
3-year-old fillies at Belmont Park. 
</P>
<P>
	What came without warning, however, was the tragedy which struck  
just prior to the running of the Mother Goose. Three Ring, 
considered one of the race's formidable entrants, reared up in the 
walking ring and fell, striking her head heavily. She was severely 
injured and was destroyed. 
</P>
<P>
	``The impact fractured her skull. It was not something that she  
could survive'' attending veterinarian Dr. Anthony Verderosa said. 
</P>
<P>
	Three Ring, winner of the Acorn Stakes at Belmont on June 4, was  
the only Mother Goose entrant still eligible for a sweep of the 
NYRA's Triple Tiara series. The daughter of Notebook won six of 10 
careers starts with two seconds and a third and earnings of 
$773,440. In addition to the Acorn, she won Gulfstream Park's 
Bonnie Miss and Davona Dale stakes. 
</P>
<P>
	Dreams Gallore swept to the lead after entering the stretch and  
won with ease over Oh What a Windfall, who 1 3/4 lengths ahead of 
Better Than Honour. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the second added-money victory this year for Dreams  
Gallore, who was second behind Silverbulletday in her prior two 
starts, the Black Eyed Susan at Pimlico and the Kentucky Oaks at 
Churchill Downs. 
</P>
<P>
	Dreams Gallore covered 1 1/8 miles in 1:48 3-5 to earn $150,000 for  
Gary A. Tanaka. It was the second victory in seven starts this year 
for the daughter of Silver Ghost. 
</P>
<P>
	``The Coaching Club American Oaks (July 24 at Belmont) would  
probably be next for her,'' trainer Steve Asmussen said. ``We'll 
probably bring her back to Churchill Downs and have her train there 
because she's flourished in that environment.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Dreams Gallore returned $3.30, $2.50 and $2.10. Oh What a  
Windfall paid $6.90 and $2.10 and Better Than Honour was worth 
$2.10. 
</P>
<P>
	Hearts At Risk sprang an upset in the co-featured Mike Lee  
Stakes for 3-year-olds. The son of Septieme Ciel came from far back 
to edge favored David by three-quarters of a length, with Brocco's 
Magick a half-length further back in third in the field of 12. 
</P>
<P>
	Hearts At Risk, ridden by Robbie Davis, earned $51,390 from a  
purse of $85,650 after going seven furlongs in 1:23 2-5. 
</P>
<P>
	Hearts At Risk, who has won three of six starts this year,  
returned $128, $24 and $10.20. David paid $2.70 and $2.40 and 
Brocco's Magick was worth $3.90. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the second big payoff on Saturday's card. Valid Victor  
won the first race and paid $128.50. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
