<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Crew 2, MetroStars 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) -- Stern John had a goal and an assist and  
Mark Dougherty set a Major League Soccer record for victories by a 
goalkeeper as the Columbus Crew beat the New York-New Jersey 
MetroStars 2-1 Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Dougherty allowed a goal to Todd Yeagley in the 80th minute en  
route to his 44th career victory, one more than Dallas' Mark Dodd. 
</P>
<P>
	John gave Columbus a 1-0 lead in the 32nd minute thanks to  
sloppy ballhandling. 
</P>
<P>
	Jeff Cunningham ran down Mike Petke's errant header and found  
Brian McBride, who one-timed a pass to John in the penalty area, 
leaving him an open shot on goalkeeper Tim Howard. 
</P>
<P>
	Columbus (9-5) took a 2-0 lead in the 68th minute when John  
dropped a pass to Brian Maisonneuve, who drove a shot from 20 yards 
past Howard for his first goal this season. 
</P>
<P>
	Yeagley scored from about 15 yards off a pass from Billy Walsh  
after Thomas Dooley failed to play the ball out of the Columbus 
zone. 
</P>
<P>
	The MetroStars (4-10) have lost sixth straight.  
  	   	
