<HEADLINE> Manistique Wins Vanity Handicap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Manistique extended her unbeaten streak  
in California to eight races Saturday night with a 4 1/2-length 
victory over Yolo Lady in the $400,000 Vanity Handicap for fillies 
and mares at Hollywood Park. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Chris McCarron, the 4-year-old filly covered 1 1/8 miles  
in 1:48. 
</P>
<P>
	Manistique's seven previous wins at Southern California tracks  
have been by an average of more than five lengths and include the 
Santa Margarita Handicap and La Canada at Santa Anita and the 
Bayakoa Handicap and Hollywood Oaks at Hollywood Park. 
</P>
<P>
	She picked up a purse of $240,000 to boost her career earnings  
for 505 Farms to $916,700. 
</P>
<P>
	As the 1-2 favorite, Manistique paid $3, $2.60 and $2.10, while  
Yolo Lady paid $5.60 and $3.60 and Bella Chiarra was $4.40 to show. 
</P>
<P>
	Also Saturday, General Challenge defeated Desert Hero by two  
lengths as they made their first starts since the Kentucky Derby in 
the $125,000 Affirmed Handicap for 3-year-olds. 
</P>
<P>
	The 3-5 favorite, General Challenge paid $3.20, $2.40 and $2.10.  
Desert Hero returned $3.40 and $2.20, while Crowning Storm paid 
$2.40 to show. 
</P>
<P>
	The victory was the fifth in seven starts for General Challenge,  
who picked up a purse of $75,000 to increase his earnings for 
Golden Eagle Farms to $717,900. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
