<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Quotes From the Spurs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Some comments from the San Antonio Spurs, who won their first  
NBA championship on Friday night with a 78-77 victory the New York 
Knicks in Game 5. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	``It was remarkable he could silence all the critics with a shot  
they said he could not hit.'' 
</P>
<P>
	-- David Robinson on the game-winning corner jump shot by Avery  
Johnson with 47 seconds left in the decisive game. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	``You know that they're going to be running that shot from the  
corner over and over. It's exciting when you're a part of it. ... 
It's just unbelievable it came down to a jump shot and not a jump 
hook from the big men or a 3-pointer from the perimeter guys. It 
came down to a jump shot from me.'' 
</P>
<P>
	-- Johnson on making the crucial basket.  
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	``Pop has been spending a lot of money on sending coaches to  
Houston to keep me working on my jumper. I wanted to make sure he 
got his money's worth.'' 
</P>
<P>
	-- Johnson on coach Gregg Popovich's efforts to help him during  
the offseason in Houston, where Johnson lives. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	``San Antonio -- this is for you, baby. It's for you.''  
</P>
<P>
	-- Tim Duncan, speaking to thousands of Spurs fans Saturday at  
the team's airport arrival. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	``My birthday's today. What a great present.''  
</P>
<P>
	-- Jerome Kersey after arriving back in San Antonio on Saturday.  
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	``The bottom line here is Avery Johnson, Sean Elliot and David  
Robinson. How could you not be thrilled for those three guys who 
have been laboring so long? That's what this is all about.'' 
</P>
<P>
	-- Popovich on the significance of winning the championship.  
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	``It feels great. That's the understatement of the millennium.''  
</P>
<P>
	-- Malik Rose, on his reaction to winning a title.  
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	``If you learn anything from this, learn that the Lord doesn't  
give up on his people. ... He takes you all the way.'' 
</P>
<P>
	-- Robinson on the championship and his faith.  
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	``It took 10 years to get here, so I figure it's going to take a  
couple of months to soak in. ... I spent most of the day just 
exhaling, really.'' 
</P>
<P>
	-- Robinson on Saturday, talking about winning a title after 10  
years in the league. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	``This is for people who make $12,000 a year and have been Spurs  
fans forever. This is about everybody in San Antonio. It's not just 
about us.'' 
</P>
<P>
	-- Johnson after being greeted by the crowd at San Antonio  
International Airport on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	``Numero Uno.''  
</P>
<P>
	-- Duncan upon his arrival home.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
