<HEADLINE> Clash 2, Fusion 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FORT LAUDERDALE, Fla. (AP) -- Raul Diaz Arce broke an 11-game  
scoring drought with a first-half header that lifted the San Jose 
Clash to a 2-1 victory over the Miami Fusion on Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Diaz Arce, Major League Soccer's leading career scorer entering  
this season, broke a 1-1 tie in the 35th minute by heading home a 
cross from El Salvador countryman Ronald Cerritos. 
</P>
<P>
	It was only the second goal this season for Diaz Arce, who came  
to the Clash from New England before the season. Jeff Baicher 
scored in the 21st minute as the Clash (9-6) claimed only their 
second win this season in regulation time. 
</P>
<P>
	Welton's 12th-minute goal was the only scoring for Miami (4-12),  
which has lost four consecutive games and nine of 10. 
</P>
<P>
	Diaz Arce's goal began with a run down the left flank by  
Cerritos and ended with an open header from six yards. It was Diaz 
Arce's first goal since April 3 against Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
	San Jose goalkeeper Joe Cannon preserved the lead in the 65th  
minute with a diving save on a header by Miami's Jay Heaps. 
</P>
<P>
	The Fusion took a 1-0 lead on Welton's goal, only the third time  
this season Miami has scored first. Henry Gutierrez threaded a pass 
between three defenders to Welton, who easily beat Cannon for his 
first goal this season. 
</P>
<P>
	The Clash tied it nine minutes later on Baicher's left-footed  
shot from the top of the penalty arc. The ball deflected off 
Miami's Arley Palacios to beat goalkeeper Garth Lagerway, who was 
starting for the injured Jeff Cassar. 
</P>
<P>
	The Fusion missed two clear chances to reclaim the lead within a  
four-minute span midway through the first half. Jeremy Aldrich had 
a header cleared off the goal line by San Jose's Joey Martinez, and 
Cannon thwarted a one-on-one chance by Diego Serna. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
