<HEADLINE> NHL Draft Transactions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ANAHEIM MIGHTY DUCKS--Traded the 15th pick and C Travis Green to  
Phoenix for D Oleg Tverdovsky. 
</P>
<P>
	ATLANTA THRASHERS--Traded F Phil Crowe to Nashville for future  
considerations. Traded the 184th pick for F Per Svartvadet. 
</P>
<P>
	CALGARY FLAMES--Traded the ninth pick, the 77th pick and the  
rights to Jan Hlavec to the New York Rangers for the 11th pick in 
the first round and C Marc Savard. 
</P>
<P>
	CHICAGO BLACKHAWKS--Traded the 249th pick to Washington for a  
seventh-round pick in 2000. 
</P>
<P>
	COLORADO AVALANCHE--Traded the 268th pick to the New York  
Islanders for a ninth-round pick in the 2000 draft. 
</P>
