<HEADLINE> Wittman Interviews For Cavs' Job </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CLEVELAND (AP) -- Minnesota Timberwolves assistant coach Randy  
Wittman returned Saturday for a second interview for the Cleveland 
Cavaliers' head coaching job. 
</P>
<P>
	He was the second candidate invited back for a follow-up  
interview. Former Charlotte coach Dave Cowens had a second 
interview on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Wittman, a Minnesota assistant for the past six years, told  
WOIO-TV in an airport interview that he was excited to get a second 
interview because it means he's still in the running to replace 
Mike Fratello, who was fired June 1. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's something I've been waiting for since I retired as a  
player seven years ago,'' Wittman said. ``Whatever happens, it's 
really good experience for me. I've learned a lot in this process. 
It's exciting to have this opportunity.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Others believes to have had initial interviews with the Cavs  
include former Lakers coach Del Harris and former Notre Dame and 
NBA coach John MacLeod. 
</P>
<P>
	Officials with the Cavaliers, who have largely conducted the  
coaching search in secret, could not be reached for comment 
Saturday night. A message seeking comment was left at team offices. 
  	   	
</P>
