<HEADLINE> Chilukki Wins Debutante at Churchill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) -- Chilukki remained undefeated in three  
career starts and cruised to a 5 1/4-length victory over Miss 
Wineshine in the $112,900 Grade III Debutante for 2-year-old 
fillies Saturday at Churchill Downs. 
</P>
<P>
	Chilukki, ridden by Willie Martinez and trained by Bob Baffert,  
covered the 5 1/2 furlongs in a stakes record 1:03.66 and paid $2.60, 
$2.20 and $2.10 as the 2-5 favorite. 
</P>
<P>
	Miss Wineshine, ridden by Sal Gonzalez and also trained by  
Baffert, closed from fifth on the backside and paid $4.60 and 
$2.10. Cecilia's Crown, with Brian Peck aboard, finished another 1 1/4 
lengths back in third and paid $2.10. 
</P>
<P>
	Chilukki earned $69,998 to increase her lifetime winnings to  
$202,723. In her last race on May 31, the daughter of Cherokee Run 
beat six males in the Kentucky Breeders' Cup. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
