<HEADLINE> News Corp. Magnate Murdoch Marries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- News Corp. chairman Rupert Murdoch and  
television executive Wendi Deng were married aboard his yacht in 
New York Harbor. 
</P>
<P>
	Eighty-two guests attended the private ceremony Friday evening  
aboard ``Morning Glory,'' which left from Chelsea Piers as a string 
ensemble played Mozart. The couple were married by state Supreme 
Court Justice Jacqueline Silbermann. 
</P>
<P>
	Among the guests were family members and friends including  
Michael Milken and Russian entrepreneur Boris Berezovsky. Welsh 
singing prodigy Charlotte Church performed three songs at the 
service. 
</P>
<P>
	Murdoch's divorce from his second wife, Anna, was finalized June  
8, ending their 32-year marriage. Details of the settlement were 
not disclosed, but in a joint statement the couple described the 
agreement as amicable, and said management of Murdoch's media 
empire would not be affected. 
</P>
<P>
	Murdoch, 68, controls 30.1 percent of News Corp., the  
international media conglomerate that includes the 20th Century Fox 
movie studio, Fox TV, the Los Angeles Dodgers, major newspapers in 
the United States, England and Australia and satellite TV networks 
on several continents. 
</P>
<P>
	His net worth was estimated by Forbes magazine this year at $7.2  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
	Deng, 32, resigned from her post as vice president of Murdoch's  
Hong Kong-based Star Television service late last year. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
