<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Norway 4, Japan 0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Norway lost captain Linda Medalen to a broken  
nose early in the match. That didn't slow the defending champions 
one bit Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
	The Norwegians scored three first-half goals and rolled to a 4-0  
victory over Japan to stay unbeaten through three games of the 
women's World Cup. 
</P>
<P>
	Unni Lehn had two assists and was responsible for Norway's  
second goal when her shot went off Japan's Hiromo Isozaki and into 
the net. 
</P>
<P>
	To celebrate the victory, Norway's players raced around the  
soggy turf and did belly flops and bowed for the fans who were left 
at rainy Soldier Field. Attendance for the doubleheader was 34,256. 
</P>
<P>
	Norway will face Sweden, a 2-0 winner Saturday over Ghana, in  
Wednesday's quarterfinals at San Jose, Calif. 
</P>
<P>
	Norway got started early as Hege Riise scored on a penalty kick  
in the eighth minute after teammate Monica Knudsen was taken down 
in the penalty area by Isozaki. 
</P>
<P>
	Two minutes later, Medalen, once a big-time scorer who is now a  
tough defender, had to leave the game after butting heads with a 
Japanese player as they positioned for a header. 
</P>
<P>
	It was 2-0 when Lehn's shot from the right side went off Isozaki  
and deflected into the goal in the 26th minute. The lead increased 
when Lehn lobbed a shot into the box where Ann Kristin Aarones 
stopped the ball, let it drop and then beat goalie Nozomi Yamago in 
the 36th minute. 
</P>
<P>
	Dagny Mellgren's header from Lehn's pass gave Norway a 4-0 lead  
in the 61st minute. 
</P>
<P>
	Japan was 0-2-1 in Group C competition.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
