<DOCNO> APW19990626.0136 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-26 17:44:18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Boxer 'Bonecrusher' Smith Retires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BUIES CREEK, N.C. (AP) -- James ``Bonecrusher'' Smith will  
announce his retirement because of a shoulder injury. 
</P>
<P>
	The 46-year-old Smith dislocated his right shoulder in a bout  
with Joe Bugner in Australia on July 4, 1998, and had to stop the 
fight after the first round. 
</P>
<P>
	He once again encountered shoulder problems in his Legends of  
Boxing heavyweight bout against Larry Holmes in Fayetteville on 
June 18, and finally signaled his corner to halt the fight two 
minutes into the eighth round. 
</P>
<P>
	``I had the shoulder checked at the hospital the day after the  
fight and it wasn't dislocated,'' Smith said. ``It was very 
painful, and they said it would probably be a recurring 
condition.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Smith has announced his retirement before but this is the first  
time such a decision has been based on physical reasons. 
</P>
<P>
	``I hope to continue as a consultant to Legends of Boxing,''  
Smith said. ``The next time they have a news conference, I will 
make a formal announcement about my retirement.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Smith has a career record of 43-16-1 with 31 knockouts. He  
stopped Tim Witherspoon in the first round at Madison Square Garden 
on Dec. 12, 1986, for the WBA title. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
