<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Orosco's Sets Relief Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BALTIMORE (AP) -- Jesse Orosco, the Baltimore Orioles'  
left-handed relief specialist, pitched in his 1,051st game Friday 
night, breaking Kent Tekulve's record for career appearances by a 
reliever. 
</P>
<P>
	Orosco, 42, a 20-year veteran, was summoned by Orioles manager  
Ray Miller with one out in the eighth inning to protect an 8-7 
Baltimore lead over the New York Yankees. 
</P>
<P>
	Orosco surrendered a game-tying single to Bernie Williams and  
got Paul O'Neill on a grounder to shortstop. He then issued an 
intentional walk to Chili Davis before being lifted in favor of 
right-hander Mike Timlin. 
</P>
<P>
	Orosco has pitched in 1,055 games, 16 short of the record held  
by Dennis Eckersley. Orosco's 30 appearances this season lead the 
Orioles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990626.0143 </DOCNO>
