<HEADLINE> Brief Summary of Wimbledon Results </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WIMBLEDON, England (AP) -- A brief look at what happened Saturday  
on the sixth day of the Wimbledon tennis championships: 
</P>
<P>
	Weather -- Mainly sunny and hot. Light rain and failing light  
halted play on the outside courts at 1 p.m. EDT. High temperature 
was 25 C (77 F). 
</P>
<P>
	Attendance -- 37,960, a record. Last year on the sixth day  
attendance was 35,008. Previous record for the first Saturday was 
35,234 in 1985. The total attendance so far is 230,552, an increase 
of 19,647 over last year. 
</P>
<P>
	Seeded winners -- Men: No. 2 Pat Rafter, No. 4 Andre Agassi, No.  
8 Todd Martin, No. 10 Goran Ivanisevic, No. 11 Gustavo Kuerten, 
</P>
<P>
	Upsets: No. 5 Richard Krajicek loses to Swiss qualifier Lorenzo  
Manta, No. 14 Tommy Haas loses to Australian qualifier Wayne 
Arthurs. 
</P>
<P>
	Seeded winners -- Women: No. 3 Lindsay Davenport, No. 5 Jana  
Novotna, No. 9 Mary Pierce, No. 14 Barbara Schett. 
</P>
<P>
	Upsets: No. 11 Julie Halard-Decugis loses to qualifier Alexandra  
Stevenson. 
</P>
<P>
	Statistic of the Day -- Australian qualifier Wayne Arthurs has  
held 60 consecutive services games at Wimbledon. 
</P>
<P>
	Quote of the Day -- ``I have a goal to win this tournament. I set  
the goal when I was nine -- to win Wimbledon by the age of 19,'' 
18-year-old qualifier Alexandra Stevenson after reaching the fourth 
round. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
