<HEADLINE> DeJean, Leyland ejected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Rockies pitcher Mike DeJean and manager Jim  
Leyland were ejected by home plate umpire Tom Hallion in a wild 
scene in the seventh inning of Saturday night's game against the 
San Diego Padres. 
</P>
<P>
	DeJean complained to Hallion on his way to the dugout after  
being replaced by Dave Veres and was quickly ejected. DeJean was 
pushed back by pitching coach Milt May and catcher Jeff Reed. 
</P>
<P>
	Hallion started to walk away, then turned and charged toward  
DeJean, who was still being restrained. Reed turned and started 
going after Hallion, but was restrained by batting coach Clint 
Hurdle. 
</P>
<P>
	Leyland and Hallion began arguing, and the manager was tossed.  
Reed stayed in the game. 
</P>
<P>
	DeJean walked three batters in 1 1-3 innings and the Rockies  
walked 10 through seven. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
