<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Truck Driver Finds Wife, Son Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SANGER, Calif. (AP) -- A tow-truck driver making a routine stop  
at a wreck Friday discovered that his wife and son had been killed 
in the accident. 
</P>
<P>
	Paul Gonzalez was called by the California Highway Patrol to tow  
cars from the wreck at about 11 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
	His wife, Brenda Lee, 28, and their son, Jacob Paul, 3, were  
killed when her car suddenly lost control, turned on its side and 
skidded into another vehicle, the patrol said. 
</P>
<P>
	The couple's daughter, Heather, 2, was hospitalized in critical  
condition Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
	The driver of the other car, Betty Almanzar, 63, was airlifted  
to a hospital with major injuries, the patrol said. 
</P>
<P>
	Jack Hudson, who runs a towing company, said the highway patrol  
chooses towing companies at random from a list. Gonzalez, who also 
runs an upholstery business, just happened to be chosen that day, 
Hudson said. 
</P>
<P>
	``Paul's got one child in the hospital right now, so he's just  
trying to do his best to regain his composure and to deal with 
this,'' Hudson said. 
</P>
<P>
	Sanger is about 200 miles southeast of San Francisco.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
